{
  "title": "Oversmack",
  "children": [
    {
      "title": "Overview",
      "lines": [
        "Smack with the whole",
        "Move surface as a",
        "step-FX editor.",
        "",
        "Reads Move's input",
        "(mic, line, USB-C)",
        "and keeps running",
        "while suspended.",
        "",
        "Open it from the",
        "overtake menu",
        "(Shift+Vol+Jog).",
        "Back hides the UI;",
        "audio keeps going.",
        "Shift+Vol+Jog exits."
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Quick Start",
      "lines": [
        "1. Set Loop Len.",
        "2. Play something",
        " into Move's input.",
        "3. Hit Capture to",
        " grab the last",
        " loop length.",
        "4. Press a step,",
        " then tap a pad in",
        " the upper rows to",
        " set its effect.",
        "5. Re-Roll for a",
        " new random",
        " pattern; edits",
        " stay locked."
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "The Grid",
      "lines": [
        "Steps 1-16: the",
        "slice pattern, one",
        "color per effect,",
        "white is playhead.",
        "Press to select a",
        "slice for editing",
        "(shown green).",
        "",
        "Upper 3 pad rows:",
        "effect palette.",
        "Row 2 left = Clean,",
        "then the 22 FX in",
        "engine order.",
        "Top-right pad =",
        "Unlock (back to",
        "the seeded roll).",
        "",
        "Bottom row:",
        "Capture, Arm, A/B,",
        "Re-Roll, Clear.",
        "",
        "Play button still",
        "controls Move.",
        "",
        "Loops over 16",
        "slices:",
        "turn the jog wheel",
        "to page through the",
        "steps."
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Knobs",
      "lines": [
        "1: FX Density",
        "2: Order Density",
        "3: Loop Length",
        "4: Slice Res",
        "5: Wet",
        "6: Pitch Range",
        "7: AB Quantize",
        "8: Seed"
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Editing & Locks",
      "lines": [
        "Tapping a palette",
        "pad pins that",
        "effect to the",
        "selected slice.",
        "Pinned slices keep",
        "their effect when",
        "you Re-Roll; the",
        "screen shows *pin.",
        "",
        "Press the same step",
        "again to clear the",
        "selection.",
        "",
        "HOLD Re-Roll to",
        "clear every pin",
        "and roll a fresh",
        "pattern.",
        "",
        "Unlock (top-right",
        "pad) un-pins just",
        "the selected slice."
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Dual Mono",
      "lines": [
        "Dual Mono treats L",
        "and R inputs as two",
        "mono signals, each",
        "with its own effect",
        "pattern, panned",
        "into the stereo",
        "field (Pan L/Pan R).",
        "",
        "Bottom pad row 7:",
        "toggle the mode.",
        "Pad 8: tap = edit L",
        "or R lane; hold +",
        "knob 1 or 2 = pans.",
        "",
        "A side plays the",
        "raw stereo loop;",
        "B side plays the",
        "panned lanes."
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Seed & Re-Roll",
      "lines": [
        "Seed browses",
        "patterns by number:",
        "the same seed always",
        "gives the same",
        "pattern.",
        "",
        "Re-Roll varies the",
        "current seed for a",
        "fresh pattern; dial",
        "the Seed knob to",
        "return to the",
        "canonical one."
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Feedback Guard",
      "lines": [
        "Speakers on with no",
        "line-in cable means",
        "the internal mic",
        "can feed back.",
        "",
        "When that risk is",
        "present the input",
        "monitoring is muted",
        "automatically: the",
        "Monitor pad turns",
        "red, capture still",
        "works, and the loop",
        "stays audible.",
        "",
        "Tap the Monitor pad",
        "to override, or",
        "plug in headphones",
        "or a line-in cable",
        "to restore it."
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "BPM Detect",
      "lines": [
        "Shift + Capture",
        "listens to the last",
        "8 seconds of input",
        "and detects its",
        "tempo (60-180 BPM).",
        "",
        "The result becomes",
        "the free-run tempo,",
        "so Capture grabs",
        "true bars of the",
        "source. Shown as",
        "@BPM in the title.",
        "",
        "MIDI clock always",
        "wins when running.",
        "Needs material with",
        "clear hits; pads",
        "and drones report",
        "no tempo."
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Sync & Transport",
      "lines": [
        "Set Move's MIDI",
        "Clock to Out so",
        "the loop locks to",
        "the transport.",
        "",
        "Without it, the",
        "loop free-runs at",
        "the project tempo.",
        "",
        "The Play button is",
        "passed through to",
        "Move, so transport",
        "and clock work",
        "under this UI."
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Screen Reader",
      "lines": [
        "With the screen",
        "reader on (Global",
        "Settings), steps,",
        "pads, knob changes",
        "and loop state are",
        "all announced."
      ]
    }
  ]
}
